I would prefer to have this logic within the constructor of the DuplicateFinder, so we could rewrite this whole block such as:
if (!regexForLiterals.hasSyntaxErrors()) {
  regexForLiterals.getResult().accept(new DuplicateFinder(mit));
}

...

private class DuplicateFinder extends RegexBaseVisitor {
  private DuplicateFinder(MethodInvocationTree mit) {
    setActiveFlags(getFlags(mit));
  }

  ...
}


Or, what about having a final method setActiveFlags(MethodInvocationTree mit) within the RegexBaseVisitor, which would itself calls the currently private getFlags(mit) ?
So in our case we could just call myVisitor.setActiveFlags(mit). I have the feeling that we will always have to call getFlags and setActiveFlags together.

